Question 1: Describe what is going on in each part of the code step-by-step. What mechanisms are being used?

if/else structure

if (condition){
  # do something
} else if (condition){
  # do this thing
} else {
  # do this
}


Works for conditions associated with singular values

Cannot do element-wise comparisons

Example: if/else statement

We can model the behavior of a single at-bat/play


if (play == "single"){
  onBase = onBase + 1
} else if (play == "homerun"){
  runs = onBase + runs + 1
  onBase = 0
} else {
  outs = outs + 1
}

