Question 2: We’ll add to the specific scenario of hitting a single, where we need to tally up a run if the number of people on base is equal to 3. Use some form of an if-else choice to do this.

Loops

For storing results from actions: use pre-filled/empty array


results &lt;- rep(NA, 10)
for (i in 1:10){
  results[i] = i
}

Breaks

Adding next in if statement can break iteration, break stops for loop

Useful if only utilizing some situations



for (i in 1:10){
  if (i &lt; 3){
    next
  } else if (i &gt; 7){
    break
  }
  print(i)
}

